documentation.title: Chat Members
documentation.description: Retrieve members of the workspace.

documentation.title: Workspace
documentation.description: Representation of a workspace. Can be ID or name, depending on the provider capability.

documentation.title: Limit
documentation.description: Maximum number of records to retrieve

documentation.title: Page
documentation.description: Page cursor retrieved from nextPage for results pagination

documentation.title: Members
documentation.description: List of retrieved members

documentation.title: Next Page
documentation.description: Cursor to the next page of listing

documentation.title: Rate Limit
documentation.description: Rate limit details.

documentation.title: Get workspace members
documentation.description: Retrieve paginated list of members

documentation.title: Id
documentation.description: Unique identifier of the member

documentation.title: Username
documentation.description: Username identifier of the member

documentation.title: Joined at
documentation.description: UNIX ms timestamp (e.g. 1095379198750) when the member joined workspace

documentation.title: Is Bot
documentation.description: Boolean that represents whether the member is a bot

documentation.title: Title
documentation.description: A short, human-readable summary of the problem type.

documentation.title: Detail
documentation.description: A human-readable explanation specific to this occurrence of the problem.

documentation.title: Rate Limit
documentation.description: Rate limit details.

documentation.title: Bucket
documentation.description:
Different parts of API may have different rate limits.
Bucket identifies to which part of API the rate limits apply.

documentation.title: Total Requests
documentation.description: Total requests available in the time window.

documentation.title: Remaining Requests
documentation.description: Remaining requests available in the time window.

documentation.title: Remaining Requests available in percents
documentation.description: Remaining requests available in the time window in percents.

documentation.title: Reset Timestamp
documentation.description: Timestamp when the rate limits will reset (in Unix Timestamp ms format).

documentation.title: Reset After
documentation.description: Number of seconds until reset of rate limit

documentation.title: Retry After
documentation.description: Number of seconds until user can retry the request
